abstract: Companies reported strong earnings and the jobless rate declined to 9 percent, sending the S.& P. higher.
snippet: Companies reported strong earnings and the jobless rate declined to 9 percent, sending the S.& P. higher.
lead_paragraph: Stocks rose on Friday, reversing losses and sending the Standard & Poor’s 500-stock index to the highest level since June 2008, after the unemployment rate unexpectedly dropped and more companies beat earnings estimates.

headline.main: S.&P. Continues to Climb as Earnings Top Estimates
headline.print_headline: S.&P. Continues to Climb As Earnings Top Estimates
